00:38:59.590 --> 00:39:00.340
TAYLOR WILSON: Hm.

00:39:00.340 --> 00:39:00.850
Interesting.

00:39:00.850 --> 00:39:01.350
All right.

00:39:01.350 --> 00:39:04.120
We'll take one more
question over here.

00:39:04.120 --> 00:39:06.730
AUDIENCE: First off,
thank you for being here.

00:39:06.730 --> 00:39:08.890
Second, thank you
for being somebody

00:39:08.890 --> 00:39:11.980
else who had a question
about the Kardashev Scale.

00:39:11.980 --> 00:39:14.620
So I had to kind of think
of something new that's

00:39:14.620 --> 00:39:16.510
still in kind of the same vein.

00:39:16.510 --> 00:39:20.110
So my question
would be how long do

00:39:20.110 --> 00:39:23.778
you think it will be before
we actually really begin

00:39:23.778 --> 00:39:24.820
to register on the scale?

00:39:24.820 --> 00:39:26.980
And what can each
of us as individuals

00:39:26.980 --> 00:39:30.370
do to kind of do
our part in society

00:39:30.370 --> 00:39:33.790
to push it that way before
we destroy ourselves

00:39:33.790 --> 00:39:35.560
as a civilization?

00:39:35.560 --> 00:39:37.510
MICHIO KAKU: Well,
on this question

00:39:37.510 --> 00:39:42.190
I actually differ with
many other scientists.

00:39:42.190 --> 00:39:46.120
Most scientists would say that
technology has no direction,

00:39:46.120 --> 00:39:47.860
no moral direction.

00:39:47.860 --> 00:39:50.830
Science is a sword,
a double-edged sword.

00:39:50.830 --> 00:39:54.610
One side can cut against
disease, ignorance, poverty.

00:39:54.610 --> 00:39:57.130
The other side can
cut against people.

00:39:57.130 --> 00:39:58.880
I disagree.

00:39:58.880 --> 00:40:01.960
I think technology does
have a moral direction.

00:40:01.960 --> 00:40:05.830
Because the internet
spreads information.

00:40:05.830 --> 00:40:08.650
Information gives
you empowerment.

00:40:08.650 --> 00:40:11.350
Empowerment gives you democracy.

00:40:11.350 --> 00:40:16.840
And democracies do not war
with other democracies.

00:40:16.840 --> 00:40:19.030
Let's do a science experiment.

00:40:19.030 --> 00:40:25.840
Write down every single war
you had to memorize as a child

00:40:25.840 --> 00:40:29.290
since you were in grade
school, every single war.

00:40:29.290 --> 00:40:32.620
Every war has been fought
between kings, emperors,

00:40:32.620 --> 00:40:39.790
queens, dictators, but never
between two major democracies.

00:40:39.790 --> 00:40:44.050
And so I think we are entering
a new moral dimension where

00:40:44.050 --> 00:40:47.440
technology is changing
the way humans

00:40:47.440 --> 00:40:50.260
interact with other
humans so that we don't

00:40:50.260 --> 00:40:53.680
tolerate dictatorships so much.

00:40:53.680 --> 00:40:56.410
When I was young, in
our history class,

00:40:56.410 --> 00:41:00.940
we learned something
called dictator for life.

00:41:00.940 --> 00:41:02.230
You had Russia.

00:41:02.230 --> 00:41:03.670
You had the United States.

00:41:03.670 --> 00:41:07.540
If you were a pawn of
Russia or a pawn of America,

00:41:07.540 --> 00:41:09.350
you were there forever.

00:41:09.350 --> 00:41:12.940
The only way to take you out
of power is through a coffin.

00:41:12.940 --> 00:41:17.120
Dictator for life--
today, we laugh at that.

00:41:17.120 --> 00:41:19.030
I mean, dictators for life--

00:41:19.030 --> 00:41:20.920
I mean, come on, right?

00:41:20.920 --> 00:41:22.040
We have the internet.

00:41:22.040 --> 00:41:23.500
We have empowerment.

00:41:23.500 --> 00:41:25.030
We have knowledge.

00:41:25.030 --> 00:41:29.120
And so dictators are
endangered species now.

00:41:29.120 --> 00:41:32.830
So I think that technology
does have a moral direction.

00:41:32.830 --> 00:41:36.130
I think it is liberating,
it is empowering,

00:41:36.130 --> 00:41:39.010
and it is changing
world history.

00:41:39.010 --> 00:41:40.870
A new chapter in
world history is

00:41:40.870 --> 00:41:43.750
being written as
individuals make

00:41:43.750 --> 00:41:47.508
their mark on human history.

00:41:47.508 --> 00:41:48.550
TAYLOR WILSON: All right.

00:41:48.550 --> 00:41:49.420
Well, thank you all.

